        <main>
            <h1><%= cat %>DID/VC</h1>
            <h2>About</h2>
                <p>In this page, you can create your own DID/VC. Your DID will be stored in this page. You can download your VC via API.</p>
                <p>About DID, please show <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/did-core/">here</a>.</p>
                <p>About VC, please show <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/vc-data-model-2.0/">here</a>.</p>
            <h2>Usage</h2>
                <h3>Create DID</h3>
                    <p>First, you have to make your DID to create VC. To make create DID, please click "CREATE DID" button.</p>
                <h3>Create VC</h3>
                    <p>Now you can create your VC. Click "CREATE VC" button, and enter your username.</p>
                <h3>Download VC</h3>
                    <p>You can download your VC via API as JSON. Please visit "/api/username/YOUR_USERNAME"</p>
                <h3><i>Note</i></h3>
                    <p><i>Name for creating DID/VC shoudn't be conflicted. If you have worry about your name, please show <a href="did">here</a> and find a name which you want to use.</i></p>
